-- Raiffeisen Bank International says not in talks with Hungary
-- By Michael Shields
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 05:00AM EST
-- None



VIENNA, Dec 18 (Reuters) - Raiffeisen Bank International <RBIV.VI> said on Thursday it was not in discussions with Hungary's government after a top official called Austrian banks strategic partners for Budapest. [ID:nL6N0U14U9]

"There are no negotiations, no decisions," an RBI spokeswoman said by email.